w that twisted\nmagnetic field structures are created at the locations hosting eruptions in\nCBPs. These twisted structures are produced by footpoint motions imposed by\nchanges in the photospheric magnetic field observations. The true nature of the\nmicro-flares remains unknown. Further 3D data-driven MHD modelling is required\nto show how these twisted regions become unstable and erupt.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 28 Jan 2019 18:38:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-03-13"}
